pavilion /pəˈvɪljən/

(pavilions) 

1. N-COUNT A pavilion is a large temporary structure such as a tent that is used at outdoor public events. (为举行户外活动而搭建的诸如帐篷的) 大的临时建筑物 

例： ...heading across the beautiful green lawn toward the International Pavilion. …穿过美丽的绿草坪前往国际展篷。 

2. N-COUNT A pavilion is an ornamental building in a garden or park. 亭子 

例： Despite persistent rain showers, the lawn and pavilion were packed with fans. 尽管有持续阵雨，草坪上和亭子里还是挤满了仰慕者。

